<div id="review_956875922" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/956875922" />
    <a title=" Eldritch_Reading_Reindeer Groundhogged" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7302570-eldritch-reading-reindeer-groundhogged"><img alt=" Eldritch_Reading_Reindeer Groundhogged" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1585161068p2/7302570.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/956875922?book_show_action=true">Jun 03, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title=" Eldritch_Reading_Reindeer Groundhogged" class="user" itemprop="url" name=" Eldritch_Reading_Reindeer Groundhogged" href="/user/show/7302570-eldritch-reading-reindeer-groundhogged"> Eldritch_Reading_Reindeer Groundhogged</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7302570-eldritch-reading-reindeer-groundhogged?shelf=armchair-pacificnw-us">armchair-pacificnw-us</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7302570-eldritch-reading-reindeer-groundhogged?shelf=a1-edelweiss-reviewed">a1-edelweiss-reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7302570-eldritch-reading-reindeer-groundhogged?shelf=2014_reads">2014_reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7302570-eldritch-reading-reindeer-groundhogged?shelf=a1-i-own-books">a1-i-own-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7302570-eldritch-reading-reindeer-groundhogged?shelf=a1-netgalley">a1-netgalley</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7302570-eldritch-reading-reindeer-groundhogged?shelf=armchair-new-england">armchair-new-england</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7302570-eldritch-reading-reindeer-groundhogged?shelf=literary-my-challenge">literary-my-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7302570-eldritch-reading-reindeer-groundhogged?shelf=september-2014-reads">september-2014-reads</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer956875922" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16260934259326944348">REVIEW: A SUDDEN LIGHT by Garth Stein<br/><br/>I had never before read any of Garth Stein &apos;s novels, though I own a Kindle copy of THE ART OF RACING IN THE RAIN. From the first pages of A SUDDEN LIGHT I was enraptured, fascinated, and engrossed. This is a very special novel, an exceptional one. With a plethora of delicately peeled character studies, a multiply hot-button plot, and the ease with which history intertwines with contemporary, and Supernatural with consensus reality--not to mention truly Faulk</span>
  <span id="freeText16260934259326944348" style="display:none">REVIEW: A SUDDEN LIGHT by Garth Stein<br /><br />I had never before read any of Garth Stein 's novels, though I own a Kindle copy of THE ART OF RACING IN THE RAIN. From the first pages of A SUDDEN LIGHT I was enraptured, fascinated, and engrossed. This is a very special novel, an exceptional one. With a plethora of delicately peeled character studies, a multiply hot-button plot, and the ease with which history intertwines with contemporary, and Supernatural with consensus reality--not to mention truly Faulknerian overtones--A SUDDEN LIGHT is a colossus of a novel: not in length but in status--definitely one of the BEST books of 2014.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16260934259326944348" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


