<div id="review_1920444484" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1920444484" />
    <a title="Bandit" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4528663-bandit"><img alt="Bandit" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1289488158p2/4528663.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1920444484?book_show_action=true">Feb 21, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bandit" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bandit" href="/user/show/4528663-bandit">Bandit</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook 9781442353244" href="/book/show/13547761-a-sudden-light">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1920444484" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17493632592537146154">A boy and his father returns to their ancestral home to address the ghosts of the past, real and otherwise, residing there. I actually had some reservations about this one, thought it might be too YA, having a 14 year old protagonist, but alas, Clever Trevor turned out to be just smart and mature enough to avoid the trappings of young adults simplicity. Predictable in parts, but very engaging and entertaining story and very well read by the narrator, this story was a good company for several lon</span>
  <span id="freeText17493632592537146154" style="display:none">A boy and his father returns to their ancestral home to address the ghosts of the past, real and otherwise, residing there. I actually had some reservations about this one, thought it might be too YA, having a 14 year old protagonist, but alas, Clever Trevor turned out to be just smart and mature enough to avoid the trappings of young adults simplicity. Predictable in parts, but very engaging and entertaining story and very well read by the narrator, this story was a good company for several long walks. It maintained my interest throughout and stayed fresh in memory in between. Recommended.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17493632592537146154" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


